sense.def:
A tick
je pisno znamenje *5X013. Z njim pokažemo, da je nekaj pravilno ali opravljeno.

seg.quote: There was a red tick in the margin.

sense.def:
To tick something
pomeni narediti kljukico ob nečem, kar je napisano na papirju.

Kadar ura
ticks
, oddaja kratke zvoke v rednih razmikih.

seg.quote: I could hear my wristwatch ticking away.
She could hear a faint ticking.

sense.def:
The tick of a clock or watch
je vrsta kratkih zvokov, ki jih povzroča ura, ki teče.

seg.quote: The clock in the kitchen had a noisy tick.

sense.def:
Kadar nekaj
makes someone tick
, je vzrok za človekov značaj ali vedênje.

Kadar sekunde, minute ali ure
tick by
, minevajo.

seg.quote: The seconds ticked by and still they heard no explosion.

sense.def:
To tick off an item on a list
pomeni narediti kljukico ob točki na seznamu kot znak, da je tista točka rešena ali opravljena.

To tick someone off
pomeni z nekom govoriti jezno, ker je nekaj naredil narobe;

seg.quote: David had ticked her off for being careless.

sense.def:
Kadar nekaj
ticks over
, deluje redno, vendar ne tako dobro ali s polno močjo, kot bi lahko.

seg.quote: ...enough to keep the essential processes ticking over for a few months.
